Mending the MELD: An in-depth review of the past, present, and future portopulmonary hypertension MELD exception.
Thus, in February 2021, the Organ Procurement Transplantation Network (OPTN) approved proposed modifications to POPH MELD exception criteria, now allowing either of the following post-treatment, pre-LT hemodynamic profiles: mPAP less than 35 mmHg and post-treatment PVR less than 400 dynes*sec/cm5 (or less than 5 WU) or mPAP greater than or equal to 35 mmHg and less than 45 mmHg and post-treatment PVR less than 240 dynes*sec/cm5 (or less than 3 WU). This article reviews the history of the POPH MELD exception, describes the recent modifications to the exception criteria and the evidence supporting them, and also highlights unanswered questions and areas for future research.
