Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
Review article: Diagnosis and investigation of irritable bowel syndrome.
Hydrogen breath tests for lactose malabsorption or small intestinal bacterial overgrowth have no role in the routine assessment of suspected IBS. Adopting a standardised approach to the diagnosis and investigation of IBS will help to promote high-quality and high-value care for patients overall.
